HEADWORD: Dew-point
<hw>Dew"-point`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Meteor.)</fld>
<def>The temperature at which dew begins to form. It varies with the
humidity and temperature of the atmosphere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

